Package: vaccine
Title: Statistical Tools for Immune Correlates Analysis of Vaccine Clinical
    Trial Data
Version: 0.1.5
Authors@R: c(
    person("Avi", "Kenny", email = "avi.kenny@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9465-7307")),
    person("Nima", "Hejazi", email = "nh@nimahejazi.org",
           role = "aut",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7127-2789"))
  )
Description: Semiparametric and nonparametric statistical tools for immune
    correlates analysis of vaccine efficacy clinical trial data. This includes
    calculation of summary statistics and estimation of risk, vaccine efficacy,
    controlled risk, and controlled vaccine efficacy based on Gilbert P, Fong
    Y, Kenny A, and Carone, M (2022) <doi:10.1093/biostatistics/kxac24>. Also
    included are semiparametric-efficient, causal machine learning estimators
    of stochastic vaccine efficacy (SVE) as initially studied in Hejazi N, van
    der Laan M, Janes H, Gilbert P, Benkeser D (2021) <doi:10.1111/biom.13375>.
